HEADWORD: Scientist
<hw>Sci"en*tist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One learned in
science; a scientific investigator; one devoted to scientific study; a
savant.</def> <mark>[Recent]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Twenty years ago I ventured to propose one [a name for
the class of men who give their lives to scientific study] which has
been slowly finding its way to general adoption; and the word
<xex>scientist</xex>, though scarcely euphonious, has gradually assumed
its place in our vocabulary.</note> <rj><au>B. A. Gould (Address,
1869).</au></rj> <-- MW10 gives 1834 as first ref. date. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

